Generate Images and Video with thermal camera AMG8833
Images:
Go to the following Google Colab notebook: Generate Images Notebook
Run the notebook:
Click the "Run" arrow symbol at the top left of each code cell 
When prompted, attach the txt file generated by the thermal camera. Example: ThermalCameraAMG.txt by clicking the "Choose Files" button in the file upload dialog.

Download the generated images:
Once the code has finished running, a ZIP file containing the generated images will be downloaded automatically.
Extract the ZIP file:
Locate the downloaded output_images.zip file on your local machine.
Right-click on the ZIP file and select "Extract All" to unzip the contents.
You will now have access to all the generated images in the extracted folder.
Video:
Go to the following Google Colab notebook: Create Video Notebook
Run the notebook:
Click the "Run" arrow symbol at the top left of each code cell 
When prompted, attach the txt file generated by the thermal camera. Example: ThermalCameraAMG.txt by clicking the "Choose Files" button in the file upload dialog.

Download the generated video:
Once the code has finished running, the video file named video.mp4 will be downloaded automatically.
NOTE:
By default, the video is being created with 2 images shown per second. If you want to change this, locate the following line in the code:
video = cv2.VideoWriter(video_file, cv2.VideoWriter_fourcc(*'mp4v'), 2, (width, height))
*Change the 2 to your desired frame rate:
For 1 image per second, set fps to 1:
video = cv2.VideoWriter(video_file, cv2.VideoWriter_fourcc(*'mp4v'), 1, (width, height))
For 3 images per second, set fps to 3:
video = cv2.VideoWriter(video_file, cv2.VideoWriter_fourcc(*'mp4v'), 3, (width, height))
